    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-14T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-14T09:00:00-05:00" n="170"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.11251/89</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MIN1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-14T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 15, 6 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>767. Legation’s requests for transit licenses to Russia now being granted by
                    Swedish Government on the condition that Legation furnish certificate to the
                    effect that nothing stands in the way of exportation to Sweden from America
                    during the current year of equivalent quantity of goods for Swedish consumption
                    together with declaration from shipper committing himself to exportation of
                    goods in question.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MIN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
